text: Frank Wall was an Irish hurler, most notable for captaining the winning Dublin team that won the 1924 All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship. A native of Freshford, County Kilkenny, he uniquely did not actually play in the final, having lost his place on the team. ==References== Category:Dublin inter-county hurlers Category:All-Ireland Senior Hurling Championship winners Category:Year of birth missing Category:Year of death missing
title: Frank Wall (hurler)
